cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper addresses the task of 6D pose estimation of known rigid objects from single input images, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses deep learning-based methods, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The problem of 6D pose estimation is also relevant to robotics, which suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the paper uses RGB-D and RGB input, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
